    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-06-28T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-06-28T16:00:00-05:00" n="63"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d63">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">142.14/2427: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-28T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 28, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>59. Your 234, June 26, 4 p.m. Should you feel that there is occasion to reply to
                    the Slovak Minister you should confine yourself to the statement that you have
                    referred his communication to the Department.</p>
                <p>For your own information the position of this Government with regard to Slovakia
                    as set forth in Radio Bulletin No. 63 of March 17, 1939<note n="13"
                        xml:id="d63fn13">See letter of March 17, 1939, from the Acting Secretary of
                        State to the Secretary of the Treasury, Department of State, <hi
                            rend="italic">Press Releases</hi>, March 18, 1939, p. 200.</note> has
                    not changed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
